org.transitime.utils

Class MapKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.transitime.utils.MapKey
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataFetcher.DbDataMapKey, ScheduleDataProcessor.TerminalDeparturesKey, ScheduleDataProcessor.TripStopKey, TravelTimesProcessor.ProcessedDataMapKey

    @Immutable
public class MapKey
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is for having a key for a map that is made up of two or three objects. Often for such keys a shortcut is taken where one simply appends strings together along with a separator character so one gets a key such as "string1|string2". But that is really clunky. Best to do it right and use this class as the key for a map.

    It is probably best to subclass this class for each type of map key so that you can make sure that the proper type of key is used for the map. Otherwise it could be confusing if one has multiple different MapKeys. An example of such a subclass is:

    public static class TripStopKey extends MapKey { private TripStopKey(String tripId, String stopId) { super(tripId, stopId); }

    Author:
    SkiBu Smith
